## Strategy Categories to Explore

Use these categories to guide research when given an open-ended request like "find me a good strategy":

### Mean Reversion
- Pairs trading (cointegration-based)
- Ornstein–Uhlenbeck process strategies
- Calendar spread reversion

### Momentum
- Cross-sectional momentum (Jegadeesh & Titman 1993)
- Time-series momentum (Moskowitz, Ooi, Pedersen 2012)
- Dual momentum (Gary Antonacci)

### Statistical / ML-Based
- Hidden Markov Model regime detection
- Kalman Filter trend following
- Hurst exponent (mean-reversion vs trend classifier)
- Linear regression slope signal

### Volatility
- ATR (Average True Range) breakout
- Volatility regime switching (low-vol entry, high-vol exit)
- Realized vs implied vol spread

### Market Microstructure
- Order flow imbalance signal
- Volume-price divergence
- VPIN (Volume-Synchronized Probability of Informed Trading)

### Good Starting Sources
- https://arxiv.org/search/?searchtype=all&query=algorithmic+trading+strategy
- https://quantpedia.com/strategies/ (categorized, with performance data)
- https://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/results.cfm (search "equity trading strategy")
- https://www.alpha-architect.com/category/factor-investing/
- https://www.quantconnect.com/research (community notebooks)

