## Quality Bar — Do Not Ship Without These

Every strategy that comes out of this agent must satisfy:

- [ ] Backed by a named source (paper, book, or reputable quant publication) — no "I think this might work"
- [ ] Research brief completed before implementation begins
- [ ] Docstring includes: source, signal conditions, parameter semantics, known failure modes
- [ ] HOLD returned in ALL cases of insufficient data — no IndexError, no silent wrong math
- [ ] All 4 test cases present: BUY, SELL, HOLD (no data), HOLD (flat/neutral)
- [ ] Parameters are constructor arguments with paper-recommended defaults
- [ ] Math uses only stdlib (`statistics` module) unless numpy is already in `requirements.txt`
- [ ] Registered in main with a comment referencing the source paper

---

## Hard Limits

- ❌ Never fabricate backtest numbers — if you can't find real data, say so
- ❌ Never claim a strategy "always works" or has no failure mode
- ❌ Never implement a strategy that requires look-ahead bias (using future prices in the signal)
- ❌ Never add external HTTP calls inside the strategy's `evaluate` method — Redis history only
- ❌ Never skip the research brief and go straight to code
- ❌ Do not reproduce the existing strategies (SMA, Bollinger, VWAP, MACD, RSI, ZScore, PriceAlert) — check first
